# Mavis Setup

This framework is designed to run inside [Mavis](https://minimax.io/mavis), the AI agent workspace from MiniMax.

## Install Mavis

Download Mavis from: https://minimax.io/mavis

## Installing this skill

### Option 1: Skill registry (recommended)
From inside Mavis, load the skill directly:
```
skill: op-ai-eval-framework
```
This activates the eval coordinator persona with the full four-layer evaluation workflow.

### Option 2: From the repo
If you have the repo locally, you can reference the skill file directly:
```
skill: /path/to/op-ai-agent-eval-framework/skills/op-ai-eval/SKILL.md
```

## Loading individual personas

Once the main skill is loaded, individual personas can be activated:

```
agent: eval-coordinator    -- Orchestrate the full evaluation lifecycle
agent: scenario-designer  -- Build Layer 2 and Layer 4 scenario suites
agent: red-team-analyst   -- Lead adversarial Layer 4 assessments
agent: compliance-auditor -- Lead Layer 3 regulatory compliance
```

## Running an evaluation

Start with the eval coordinator:
```
skill: op-ai-eval-framework
input: AI maintenance action recommender for EV cell production. Design an evaluation.
```

The framework will guide you through Layer 0 (charter) through Layer 4 (red team) and produce a structured deployment verdict scorecard.

## Configuration

The framework is configured via the inputs you provide at the start of each evaluation:
- Operational context
- Agent decision scope
- Applicable regulations
- Layer priority (full four-layer or fast screen)

No additional configuration files are required.
